messages.content: ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor is a port of the openpose-editor extension for stable-diffusion-webui, made compatible with ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor?
The purpose of ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor is to allow users to edit and manipulate poses within the ComfyUI interface.
How can you use ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor in ComfyUI?
To use ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor in ComfyUI, you need to import the 'image > OpenPose Editor' node, add a new pose, and use it like you would a 'LoadImage' node.
What happens when you make changes to a pose in ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor?
Each change you make to a pose in ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor will be saved to the input folder of ComfyUI.
Yes, ComfyUI-OpenPose-Editor is a port of the openpose-editor extension originally designed for stable-diffusion-webui.
What is the original repository for the openpose-editor extension?
The original repository for the openpose-editor extension is https://github.com/fkunn1326/openpose-editor.
